    <h lang="en">gus</h>
    <h lang="gd">gus</h>
    <p lang="en"><b>gus</b>
        <en>until, till, ...</en> is a (secondary) verb particle.</p>
    <p lang="gd">...</p>
    <p lang="en">cf. the preposition <a href="?gd=gu-preposition">gu</a></p>
    <p lang="gd">...</p>
    <p lang="en">cf. <b>gus an</b>
        <en>until</en> – <ul>
            <li>Tha i air fòrladh <m>gus am pòs i</m>. <en>She is on leave until she gets
                    married.</en></li>
        </ul>
        <xl id="temporal_gus_an-xs">
            <li>
                <gd>Cha deasaich mi am biadh <m>gus an tig thu dhachaigh</m>.</gd>
                <tr>I won’t get the meal ready until you come home.</tr>
                <ref text="605">td. 221</ref>
            </li>
            <li>
                <gd>Cosnaidh mi airgead <m>gus am bi gu leòr againn dheth</m>.</gd>
                <tr>I’ll earn money until we’ve got enough of it.</tr>
                <ref text="605">td. 221</ref>
            </li>
        </xl>
    </p>
    <p lang="gd">...</p>
    <p lang="en">Also: <b>gus nach</b> – <xl id="temporal_gus_nach-xs">
            <li>
                <gd>Cùm e <m>gus nach bi feum agad air</m>.</gd>
                <tr>Keep it until you don’t need it.</tr>
                <ref text="605">td. 221</ref>
            </li>
        </xl>
    </p>
    <p lang="gd">...</p>


    <module>
        <h>fuirich gus an</h>
        <p>cf. <a href="?gd=fuirich"><g>fuirich</g></a>
            <vb/>
            <en>wait</en>, <a href="?gd=an^particle"><g>an</g></a>.</p>
        <p>Older pedagogical examples – <xl id="fuirich-older-pedag">
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha mo mhàthair a’ sgrìobhadh litreach gu m’athair a tha air falbh.
                        Thubhairt mo mhàthair, “An téid thu do bhocsa nan litrichean leis an litir
                        seo, Iain?” “Théid,” ars Iain, “falbhaidh mi an dràsda”. “<m>Fuirich gus an
                            dùin mi i is gus an cuir mi seòladh oirre.</m> Ceannaich fhéin stamp
                        agus cuir oirre i.” [...]</gd>
                    <tr>My mother is writing a letter to my father who is away. My mother said,
                        “Will you go to the postbox with this letter, John?” “Yes, I will,” said
                        John, “I will leave now.” “Wait until I seal it and put an address on it.
                        Buy a stamp and put it on it.”[...]</tr>
                    <ref text="621">td. 5</ref>
                </li>
            </xl>
        </p>
    </module>


